<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900601-0115</DOCNO><DOCID>900601-0115.</DOCID><HL>   ATandamp;T Introduces   Device for Messages   Via Rotary Phones   ----   By Robert J. Brennan   Staff Reporter of The Wall Street Journal</HL><DATE>06/01/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5C</SO><CO>   T</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)</IN><LP>   NEW YORK -- American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co. says it'sintroducing the first answering machines that respond torotary-dial phones, making it easier for people to call homeor office to get their messages.   Owners previously were limited to using touch-tone phonesor beepers when calling home for messages. The new answeringmachines now have a human-speech synthesizer that responds toa voice command to retrieve messages, getting around thetouch-tone problem.</LP><TEXT>   The machines also are the first to store as many as fourdifferent outgoing messages to callers, the company said. Twomodels of the answering machine have two lines, permittingone caller to leave a message while another is given a signalto wait and then leave a message. ATandamp;T said the two-linemodels are designed for the growing number of households,home offices and small businesses with two telephone numbers.   ATandamp;T is introducing the machines at the ConsumerElectronics Show, which opens tomorrow in Chicago. Amongother products, the telecommunications giant is introducing atwo-line cordless telephone and a caller identification unit,which can be used with caller identification servicesprovided by local phone companies. Users who have the localservice can use the Call Display 64 to view the numbers ofincoming calls. The unit stores the numbers and times of themost recent 64 calls, whether or not they were answered.   Separately, ATandamp;T Capital Corp. said it completed itsacquisition of Encore International Inc., a computer leasingconcern. Encore will operate under the name ATandamp;T SystemsLeasing Corp., and current management will remain intact inits Bloomfield Hills, Mich., headquarters, ATandamp;T Capital said.   ATandamp;T earlier this year divided its ATandamp;T Credit Corp.subsidiary into five business units and renamed it ATandamp;TCapital. The unit offers equipment leasing and financingservices for ATandamp;T and non-ATandamp;T equipment.</TEXT></DOC>